                                    <p>A. M.</p>
                                    <p>5.—Lighted fire under after boilers.</p>
                                    <p>6.20.—Steam up, unmoored ship; hove into twelve fathoms on B.
                                        B.</p>
                                    <p>6.30.—Weighed and proceeded out of harbor working
                                        expansively, catting off at 1/5 stroke.</p>
                                    <p>8.—Trial Island West, 1½ m. Employed clearing deck and ship
                                        below.</p>
                                    <p>Noon.—Saddle Island, N. W. by N. 2 m.</p>
