                                    <p>A. M.</p>
                                    <p>Fires banked. 4.30.—Drew fires forward. 4.45.— Steam up.
                                        5.—Weighed and proceeded out to the eastward, working two
                                        after boilers expansively, cutting off at 1/6 of stroke.</p>
                                    <p>6.30.—East Point, Sangster Island, S. S. E.</p>
                                    <p>9.—Exercised at general quarters.</p>
                                    <p>10.45.—Sounded 50 fathoms.</p>
                                    <p>Noon.—Point Gray, N. 45° E. Point Roberts, S. 83° E.</p>
                                    <p>Lat. obs. 49° 8' N.</p>
                                    <table>
                                        <row>
                                            <cell/>
                                            <cell>
                                                <hi rend="italic">Tons.</hi>
                                            </cell>
