                                            <cell role="num">6</cell>
                                            <cell role="num">0</cell>
                                        </row>
                                    </table>
                                    <p>P. M.</p>
                                    <p>0.45.—Entered discolored water off Fraser’s River. 4.—Point
                                        Roberts, N. N. W. 3 m. 3.30.—Eased, stopped, came to with B.
                                        B. in Birch Bay in 7 fathoms., and veered to 32 fathoms.
                                        Banked up fires. Point Roberts, S. 83° W. Called the north
                                        point of bay, bearing N. 47° W., Point Lacy after the third
                                        lieutenant; south point of bay, a white bluff S. 41° E.,
                                        Point Nutt after the surgeon of the ship.</p>
                                    <p>Midnight.—Fires banked under after boilers.</p>
                                </cell>
