                                    </table>
                                    <p>P. M.</p>
                                    <p>Opened tea, 13.44; beef, 136.3; pork, 30.80.</p>
                                    <p>1.—Eased, stopped, and came to with B. B. in 9 fathoms.
                                        Veered to 40 fathoms, banked up fires. Points of entrance,
                                        S. 74° E., and S. 74° W. Rocky point, S. 25° W. Employed
                                        cutting wood for fuel.</p>
                                    <p>2.—Furled sails, unbent maintopsail.</p>
                                    <p>Ship’s draught—forward----14 feet.</p>
                                    <p>aft.......15 feet.</p>
                                    <p>Remaining water, 29 tons.</p>
